tedbl}{\textgreater}$\pm${\textless}/span{\textgreater} 510 kg h{\textless}span class={\textquotedbl}inline-formula{\textquotedbl}{\textgreater}{\textless}sup{\textgreater}$-$1{\textless}/sup{\textgreater}{\textless}/span{\textgreater} of which is of anthropogenic origin.This study reveals that mobile street-level measurements may miss the majority of total methane emissions, potentially due to sources located within buildings, including stoves and boilers operating on natural gas. Similarly, the CH{\textless}span class={\textquotedbl}inline-formula{\textquotedbl}{\textgreater}{\textless}sub{\textgreater}4{\textless}/sub{\textgreater}{\textless}/span{\textgreater} enhancements{\textless}span id={\textquotedbl}page6898{\textquotedbl}/{\textgreater} recorded during the mobile survey from large-area sources, such as the Alster lakes, were too small to generate GPM emission estimates with confidence, but they could nevertheless influence the emission estimates based on total column measurements.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
